description:
&lt;p&gt;The Woodland Neonatal Unit at Watford Hospital is a busy local neonatal unit (LNU) within the East of England Neonatal network. The unit admits baby requiring intensive care, high dependency and special care. In addition, we manage a 6 bedded Transitional Care Unit in postnatal ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to the provision of high quality evidence based practice and the ongoing training and education of our nursing staff to meet the needs of parents and babies incorporating family centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Clinical Practice Facilitator, who wants to work with our well established friendly neonatal team, to deliver the highest standards of neonatal care. The post holder will be working 6 shifts per month in the CPF role and 7 shifts per month on the nursing clinical roster to maintain own practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Clinical Practice Facilitator, you will be teaching and supporting existing staff as well as students from all professional backgrounds. You will be responsible for facilitating pre and post registration students, newly appointed staff, staff consolidating their skills following the neonatal course, acting as a role model to strive for the delivery of first-class patient care. You will also help in the facilitation of mandatory training and in house study days to ensure all staff remains up to date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working alongside the Practice Development Nurse to enhance the learning environment and facilitate staff development to promote continuous quality improvement of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicants must have experience of teaching and mentoring and a passion for nurse education and practice development. The applicants should have an excellent clinical knowledge, integrating theory and practice as well as an understanding of professional and current issues in Children’s nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a team player, dynamic, with excellent written and verbal communication skills and a passion for teaching and developing staff, this is an opportunity for you to influence education, development and learning within the neonatal unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a full orientation to the role and you will be supported throughout your time in the role by a friendly, knowledgeable team who look forward to working with you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing the best care for every child every day!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elvira Baker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;elvira.baker@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01923 217560&lt;/p&gt;
